        <h2 id="recipe_1">Martha's Lemon Meringue Pie</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 30 Minutes</li>
            <li>Serves: 8</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Pie crust</td>
                    <td>1</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td id="yellow">Lemon Curd</td>
                    <td>2 cups</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Cold water</td>
                    <td>1 cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td id="tan">Cornstartch</td>
                    <td>1/4 cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Large egg whites</td>
                    <td>8</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Sugar</td>
                    <td>2/3 cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Coarse salt</td>
                    <td>1/4 teaspoon</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Fit a homemade or store-bought pie crust into a 9-inch pie plate; line crust with parchment paper and fill with dried beans or pie weights. Bake until crust is lightly browned, about 45 minutes. Carefully lift and remove paper with pie weights and let crust cool.
        </p>
        <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Prepare Lemon Curd through step 1. Whisk together 1 cup cold water and 1/4 cup cornstarch add to lemon mixture along with butter in step 2 and continue as directed. Do not chill curd; pour directly into cooled crust and smooth top. Refrigerate until chilled and set, 3 hours (or up to 1 day).
        </p>
        <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a large bowl, combine egg whites, sugar and salt. Using an electric mixer, beat on medium-high until stiff peaks form. Pile meringue on pie, making sure it touches the crust all around. Bake until meringue begins to brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
        </p>
        
    <p><em>Source: <a href="https://www.marthastewart.com/340995/lemon-meringue-pie">https://www.marthastewart.com/340995/lemon-meringue-pie</a></em></p>
        <h2 id="recipe_2">Elana's Chocolate Chip Cookies</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 17 Minutes</li>
            <li>Makes: 24 cookies</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td id="tan">Blanched almond flour</td>
                    <td>2 1/2 cups</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Sea salt</td>
                    <td>1/4 teaspoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td id="tan">Baking soda</td>
                    <td>1/4 teaspoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td id="yellow">Melted butter</td>
                    <td>10 tablespoons</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td id="brown">Vanilla extract</td>
                    <td>1 tablespoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td id="brown">Agave nectar or honey</td>
                    <td>1/2 cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td id="brown">Chocolate chips</td>
                    <td>1 cup</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl</p>
        <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Stir together wet ingredients in a small bowl</p>
        <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Mix wet ingredients into dry</p>
        <p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Form 1-inch balls and press onto a parchment paper lined baking sheet</p>
        <p><strong>Step 5:</strong> Bake at 350°F for 7-10 minutes</p>
        <p><strong>Step 6:</strong> Cool and serve</p>

        
    <p><em>Source: <a href="https://elanaspantry.com/chocolate-chip-cookies/">https://elanaspantry.com/chocolate-chip-cookies/</a></em></p>
    <h2 id="recipe_3">Best Ever Banana Bread</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 1 1/2 Hours</li>
            <li>Makes: 2 levels</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>All-purpose flour</td>
                    <td>1-3/4 cups</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Sugar</td>
                    <td>1-1/2 cups</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Baking soda</td>
                    <td>1 teaspoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Salt</td>
                    <td>1/2 teaspoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Large eggs</td>
                    <td>2</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Medium ripe bananas, mashed</td>
                    <td>2</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Canola oil</td>
                    <td>1/2 cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Buttermilk</td>
                    <td>1/4 cup plus 1 tablespoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Vanilla extract</td>
                    <td>1 teaspoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Chopped walnuts</td>
                    <td>1 cup</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. In another bowl, combine the eggs, bananas, oil, buttermilk and vanilla; add to flour mixture, stirring just until combined. Fold in nuts.</p>
        <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Pour into a greased or parchment-lined 9x5-in. loaf pan. If desired, sprinkle with additional walnuts. Bake until a toothpick comes out clean, 1-1/4 to 1-1/2 hours. Cool in pan for 15 minutes before removing to a wire rack.</p>
        
    <p><em>Source: <a href="https://www.tasteofhome.com/recipes/best-ever-banana-bread/">https://www.tasteofhome.com/recipes/best-ever-banana-bread/</a></em></p>
    <h2 id="recipe_4">GF Maple Pecan Cake</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 1 1/2 Hours</li>
            <li>Makes: 1 loaf, 16 pieces</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td id="tan">All-purpose flour</td>
                    <td>1-3/4 cups</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Sugar</td>
                    <td>1-1/2 cups</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td id="brown">Baking soda</td>
                    <td>1 teaspoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Salt</td>
                    <td>1/2 teaspoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td id="yellow">Large eggs</td>
                    <td>2</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td id="yellow">Medium ripe bananas, mashed</td>
                    <td>2</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Canola oil</td>
                    <td>1/2 cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td id="yellow">Buttermilk</td>
                    <td>1/4 cup plus 1 tablespoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td id="brown">Vanilla extract</td>
                    <td>1 teaspoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td id="brown">Chopped walnuts</td>
                    <td>1 cup</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. In another bowl, combine the eggs, bananas, oil, buttermilk and vanilla; add to flour mixture, stirring just until combined. Fold in nuts.</p>
        <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Pour into a greased or parchment-lined 9x5-in. loaf pan. If desired, sprinkle with additional walnuts. Bake until a toothpick comes out clean, 1-1/4 to 1-1/2 hours. Cool in pan for 15 minutes before removing to a wire rack.</p>
        
    <p><em>Source: <a href="https://www.tasteofhome.com/recipes/best-ever-banana-bread/">https://www.tasteofhome.com/recipes/best-ever-banana-bread/</a></em></p>
